episodes.name: Fri Jan 01 2010 Part 1
episodes.overview: Steve and Becky didn't have a very good start to the year as they continued to argue about having children. "No kid of mine would amount to any good. Not with my rotten genes!" Becky declared when Steve pushed her. Will that be the end of the discussion? Meanwhile, Michelle had a motherly chat with Ryan to check that he and Sian weren't having unprotected sex, while Sophie continued to give her mate a hard time for breaking her chastity vow. Elsewhere, Audrey was annoyed when Natasha forgot they were supposed to be going to a stylists dinner party together and decided to call male escort Lewis instead. Lewis accepted the invitation much to Audrey's delight. Finally, Steve and Becky pondered whether they had rushed into getting married and what the future would hold now that they had reached such an obstacle.

episodes.name: Fri Jan 01 2010 Part 2
episodes.overview: Audrey prepared for her evening with male escort Lewis but got cold feet at the last minute. Meanwhile, Tyrone told Molly he’d been talking to the wife of a big motoring company owner in Chester and she’d hinted that they might have a job for him. Elsewhere, Becky paid the Croppers a visit to chat about her problems with Steve and to tell them that she didn’t want children. Hayley and Roy were a shoulder for her to cry on but when she returned to the Rovers it was clear that Steve was growing tired of her attitude towards starting a family. Lewis finally persuaded Audrey to leave the house with him and they shared a lovely evening together. In fact, Audrey was in such a good mood that she later offered to pay for Gail’s honeymoon as a wedding present. Finally, poor Becky spent the night on the sofa after her and Steve failed to resolve their problems.

episodes.name: Mon Jan 04 2010 Part 1
episodes.overview: Things go from bad to worse for Joe when Gail tells him that the offer on the house has fallen through. How will he ever pay off his debts now? Elsewhere, relations are strained at the Rovers as Steve and Becky argue about having kids. Becky heads over to ask the Croppers for their advice but what will they tell her? Finally, Molly is pleased when she hears that Tyrone has a job interview at a garage in Chester. Tyrone of course is oblivious as to why his wife is so keen to leave the Street.

episodes.name: Mon Jan 04 2010 Part 2
episodes.overview: Steve rolls in drunk after another row with Becky. Disgusted at the state her husband is in, Becky tells him to sleep on the sofa. episodes.name: Fri Jan 08 2010 Part 1

Elsewhere, Mary Taylor plots her return to Coronation Street when she spots Norris with another woman...

episodes.name: Fri Jan 08 2010 Part 2
episodes.overview: As Tina struggles to fight her attraction to Nick, David is suspicious there's something going on between the pair. Elsewhere, as the wedding party head back to the Rovers, Rick lies in wait for Joe. Is he about to spring a nasty surprise on the groom? Meanwhile, Ken and Peter go head to head at the council planning meeting as Peter seeks planning permission for Leanne's bar.

episodes.name: Mon Jan 11 2010 Part 1
episodes.overview: Molly tried to make amends with Tyrone on their anniversary and promised him that the second year of their marriage would be better than the first. Did she really mean it? Meanwhile, Graeme informed Rosie that there was a sexy picture of her on an advert at the bus stop but that she had a pair of men’s hands over her chest. Rosie was horrified. Elsewhere, Norris was gobsmacked to see Mary back in Weatherfield. Why has Mary returned? Finally, Kevin and Sally were furious about the grubby advert that Rosie was the star of but their feisty daughter defended herself and her new career choice. "Money talks around here and in two years I’ll be rolling in it. And where will you be mum in two years' time?" goaded Rosie. Poor Sally was shocked at her daughter's words, where would she be she wondered? Kevin was furious with Rosie and threw her out of house before comforting his tearful wife.

episodes.name: Mon Jan 11 2010 Part 2
episodes.overview: Rosie and Sophie discussed their parents' reaction to Rosie's advert and began jumping to all sorts of conclusions as to why they were being so uptight. Sophie admitted that they had been acting strangely and concluded that they must be splitting up. Meanwhile, Norris persuaded Mary to spend the evening in the Rovers so that he could avoid being cooped up in her camper van. Norris was surprised however when Mary revealed that she'd met a man on her travels. Was he jealous? Finally, Sophie and Rosie went home to confront their parents but were shocked when Sally admitted that she had breast cancer. Sophie sobbed and told them she thought they were splitting up. "We're not splitting up. We love each other and we love you too," declared Kevin as Sally hugged the girls.

Johnny assures Roy that he will take care of Carla while the cafe owner is looking after his mother, and Phelan makes a copy of Nicola's flat keys without her knowing.

episodes.name: Mon Feb 26 2018 Part 2

Carla flirts with Peter and suggests that they could do with some evidence to prove that Susie would be better off with Johnny. And during lunch, Kayla steals Craig's keys.

episodes.overview: Sally stands accused of losing £40,000 of council money, and Peter shows Johnny the birth certificate. Meanwhile, Toyah and Roy discusses her ex's relationship with Carla, and Cathy rumbles Chesney's secret crush.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 29th August 2018 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Kate gives Rana an ultimatum and Simon returns from court with a referral order, but remains fearful of giving evidence against Tyler. Mary hands out invites for Jude and Angie's surprise vow renewal ceremony, unaware that they are having marriage guidance counselling.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 29th August 2018 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Carla sets Peter a trap to see whether he is really a changed character, while Jude catches Mary and Tracy planning the vow renewal. Two masked teens grab Simon and force him into a waiting car, and Liz orders Gemma not to contact Mike.

episodes.name: Friday, 31st August 2018 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Peter and Carla guard Simon at the factory and Jude avoids Angie, knowing that she wants to talk about their crumbling marriage. Daniel suggests Kate's ultimatum in unfair and Angie walks in on Imran and Leanne at an inopportune moment.

episodes.name: Friday, 31st August 2018 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Simon backs out of testifying against Tyler, causing Leanne to take out her anger on Carla, while Jude goes into denial about the end of his marriage. Gina suggests throwing a party for Jack's homecoming and Sinead becomes jealous when Daniel turns on the charm.

episodes.name: Friday, 14th September 2018 (Part 2)

Meanwhile, Tyrone offers Evelyn a place to stay, and Imran is amazed when it appears Toyah gives him the go-ahead to date her and Leanne.

episodes.name: Tuesday, 1st January 2019
episodes.overview: Audrey pins her hopes on Lewis proving Gail wrong, and Carla pushes the boat out for Peter. Meanwhile, David meets a face from the past when his old cellmate Paul turns up on the street.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 9th January 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Audrey accuses Claudia of stealing her £80k, and Tim makes a statement to the police about what Gina found out. Elsewhere, Eileen tries to play peacemaker between Liz, Jenny and Johnny, and when Brian struggles to find a new line of work, Cathy has a brainwave.

episodes.overview: Nick tries to talk Audrey out of reporting Claudia to the police, and Tim takes a call from the prison telling him Sally has been beaten up. Meanwhile, Cathy and Rita persuade Brian to give the Kabin job a go.

When the nurse insists she must discuss her situation with an adult first, Amy leaves upset. Audrey explains to Gail and David that the dry rot is much worse than she thought - the floor has collapsed and she'll have to move out.

While Tracy remains calm, Steve flies off the handle and goes storming into the corner shop to accuse Aadi of getting Amy pregnant. Gary's gutted to hear that he's lost out on the contract for Audrey's house as she's had a cheaper quote, and Roy and Carla reminisce about Hayley over lunch in the bistro.

Desperate for some cash, Gary phones his old mate Joe.

episodes.name: Friday, 15th February 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Carla could hold the key to the arsonist's identity. Amy lies to Tracy about her pregnancy scan. Chesney springs a romantic surprise on Gemma.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 13th March 2019 (Part 2)

episodes.name: Monday, 18th March 2019 (Part 1)

episodes.name: Monday, 18th March 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Sally and Gina's row brings down the factory roof. Rana insists on going ahead with the ceremony as planned. Carla begs Peter to stay in Weatherfield.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 20th March 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: As Sally lies unconscious, trapped under the falling debris, the bodies of the protestors can be seen slumped next to each other as water from a burst pipe seeps across the floor towards a live power cable. Tim, Abi and Tyrone force their way into the factory to help before emergency services arrive to search for survivors. Suddenly a loud noise signals the last section of the roof collapsing as debris rains in on those still trapped. Elsewhere, at the wedding venue a nervous Kate paces up and down as she waits for Rana, wondering if she's had a change of heart. A phone call from Rana explains everything, will the wedding go ahead?

episodes.name: Wednesday, 20th March 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: As Kate talks to Rana on the phone she's insistent they can still go ahead with their union. Will the couple get to exchange the vows that mean so much to them? Stood outside the ruins of the factory Carla's consumed with guilt. A devastated Carla reveals that she knew the roof was unsafe but chose to ignore it. As news of a death inside the factory is delivered Carla breaks down. Elsewhere, David confronts Nick, wondering if he's to blame for the factory collapse and if he was intending to pull an insurance scam.

episodes.name: Sunday, 24th March 2019
episodes.overview: Grief stalks the street following the factory roof collapse. Carla, Nick and Gary are keen to conceal their guilt. Roy is reunited with a face from the past.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 27th March (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Sally lies unconscious in the debris of the fallen factory roof. Tim and Abi rush to the aid of the wounded protesters. Rana explains to Kate her reason for the delay. Michelle's praise spurs Ali into action, and Wayne offers to assist Roy with his research. Meanwhile, Sarah threatens to dump Gary if he keeps quiet about the Underworld roof.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 27th March (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Kate dismisses Rana's doubts about proceeding with their nuptials. Carla admits to Peter that she knew the roof was unsafe. David suspects Nick of an insurance scam. Robert returns but remains evasive about his absence, and Wayne and Brian provide Roy with a promising lead. Meanwhile, Gary finds the gate of the builder's yard unlocked.

episodes.name: Friday, 29th March 2019
episodes.overview: Daniel and Sinead bring baby Bertie home. Gary's van is vandalised and his tools stolen - is Seb to blame? Michelle defends Carla as her friend is accused of an insurance scam. Angry Robert sacks Ryan for spying on him.

episodes.name: Sunday, 31st March 2019
episodes.overview: Gary demands cash from Peter to pay off Rick. Beth and Claudia clash during Bertie's homecoming party. Gina refuses to turn a blind eye to Tim's suffering.

episodes.name: Monday, 1st April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Imran accuses Carla of covering up the truth. Sally thanks Gina for saving Tim's life. Sinead spots a business opportunity at the barber's.

episodes.name: Monday, 1st April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Robert forces Carla to come clean during Rana's memorial. Gina finally receives Sally and Tim's forgiveness. A frightening sight meets Chesney's return home.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 3rd April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Carla faces the repercussions of her confession. Chesney catches Gemma cheating in a radio phone-in quiz. Geoff brags about his gardening prowess.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 3rd April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Carla finds herself public enemy number one. Chesney berates Gemma for defrauding Mary. Rita plays matchmaker to Paul and Billy.

episodes.name: Friday, 5th April 2019
episodes.overview: Chesney tires of Gemma being irresponsible. Carla resolves to make amends to her workforce. David offers Natalie a trial at the barber's.

episodes.name: Monday, 8th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Carla receives a chilling message on Aidan's birthday. Chesney faces up to his own mortality. Nick and David encourage Natalie to quit her job.

episodes.name: Monday, 8th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Peter grows concerned as Carla begins to unravel. Emma hosts a 'Mr and Mrs' contest at the Rovers. Natalie refuses to be beaten by Nick and David.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 10th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Rick forces a reluctant Gary to work for him. Daniel suggests a naming ceremony for Bertie.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 10th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Gary despairs when Rick targets Alex. Nick looks forward to running Underworld from in the community centre.

episodes.name: Friday, 12th April 2019
episodes.overview: Peter realises the extent of Carla's paranoia. Sally disapproves of Dev and Steve joking about Tim's health, while Nick offers support to a grieving Imran. Gary is guiltridden when Alex buys Cathet a bracelet, knowing he bought it with a loan from Rick.

episodes.name: Monday, 15th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Suspicion falls on Imran when Wayne's report is stolen, and Peter informs Carla's family of her disappearance. Meanwhile, Sally implores Tim to take his condition seriously.

episodes.name: Monday, 15th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Imran maintains his innocence under police interrogation, and Kate receives Rana's personal effects. Elsewhere, Bethany tells tales to Sarah about Gary.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 17th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Gary meets a familiar face on his first day collecting debts, and Chesney and Gemma's caravan holiday starts badly. Meanwhile, Michelle lashes out at Robert.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 17th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Sarah fears Gary will be implicated in the roof sabotage, and Chesney catches Gemma fleecing Joseph at poker. Elsewhere, Nick diverts the police's attention from his crime.

episodes.name: Friday, 19th April 2019
episodes.overview: Gemma storms off following a row with Chesney. Rick clears out Gary's yard to settle his debt. Eileen takes in Jan as a paying guest at Number 11.

episodes.name: Monday, 22nd April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Sarah is sickened to discover the identity of Gary's loan shark, and Beth delights in Ken's misfortune. Meanwhile, Seb's new business gets off to a promising start

episodes.name: Monday, 22nd April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Eileen learns of Gary's latest stroke of bad luck, and Kirk aims to restore peace at Bertie's chaotic christening party. Elsewhere, Gemma predicts the end for her and Chesney

episodes.name: Wednesday, 24th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Simon helps Peter in his quest to find Carla, and Rita offers an alternative explanation for Gemma's symptoms. Meanwhile, Kirk considers pursuing a music career.Gary meets a familiar face on his first day collecting debts, and Chesney and Gemma's caravan holiday starts badly. Meanwhile, Michelle lashes out at Robert.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 24th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Peter's search leads him to Carla's childhood estate, and Gary begs Sarah for another chance. Elsewhere, Seb and Alina's first date gets cut short.

episodes.name: Friday, 26th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Peter and Johnny follow up another sighting of Carla. Chesney orders Gemma to see a doctor. Seb has a manicure in order to spend time with Alina.

episodes.name: Friday, 26th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Simon pulls Peter back from the brink. Nick receives news that fuels Toyah's suspicions. Seb dreads Alina's reaction to his HIV status.

episodes.name: Monday, 29th April 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Toyah discovers Wayne's stolen report in Nick's bedroom. Ken supports Peter as Carla's absence takes its toll. Sally overhauls Tim's diet and fitness regim.

episodes.name: Monday, 29th April 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Nick insists that someone is trying to frame him. Ken and Claudia take charge of a fragile Peter. Tim rebels against Sally's boot camp.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 1st May 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Nick's arrest puts Leanne's faith in him to the test. Sally hosts a healthy dinner party in Tim's honour. Jan worries about Mary's idea of their friendship.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 1st May 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Leanne must decide if she can stand by her man. Tim accuses Sally of trying to control him. Chesney misreads Ryan's intentions towards Gemma.

episodes.name: Friday, 3rd May 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Gemma packs her bags to go and live with her mum. Mary discovers that Jan has trifled with her affections. Nick orders David to throw Shona off the scent.

episodes.name: Friday, 3rd May 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Chesney implores Gemma not to run away. Mary reels when Freda delivers a bombshell from Norris. Yasmeen vows to prove Sally wrong.

episodes.name: Monday, 6th May 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: A hysterical Mary is stunned when Norris returns to Weatherfield, and Geoff accuses Yasmeen of doing everything she can to avoid spending time with him.

episodes.name: Monday, 6th May 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Norris reveals to Mary that he and Freda are engaged and he wants a divorce so he can marry her. Yasmeen apologises to Geoff and asks him to come back to the house.

episodes.name: Monday, 18th November 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel returns in time for the funeral, and in a moving service everyone says goodbye to Sinead before gathering at the Rovers for the wake. Michelle's behaviour confuses Carla, and Paul questions Billy's decision to employ Bernie

episodes.name: Monday, 18th November 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: As the wake continues in the Rovers, Daniel lets himself into the flat and is shocked to find it trashed. Meanwhile, Tyler and Vicky see red over Robert's betrayal, and Paul and David confide in each other

episodes.name: Wednesday, 20th November 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel is devastated to discover the laptop has gone and decides to take matters into his own hands. Meanwhile, Paul harbours suspicions of Bernie, and James seeks Michael's help to keep his secret from coming out

episodes.name: Wednesday, 20th November 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Gemma throws Bernie out of her house and Michael is rocked by a sighting of his ex-girlfriend. Meanwhile, the police arrive at the pawn shop and arrest Daniel. Can Craig and Peter persuade the owner to drop the charges by explaining the circumstances?

episodes.name: Friday, 22nd November 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Gemma and Bernie break into Kel's flat and find not only Daniel's laptop, but a stack of old photos of Paul and some other kids. Elsewhere, Michael hopes to become part of his daughter's life, and Beth calls at Daniel's flat to find him sobbing

episodes.name: Friday, 22nd November 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: As Gemma and Bernie return with the laptops and photos, Paul is horrified to see his terrible past laid before him. Elsewhere, Aggie jeopardises Michael's negotiations with Grace, and Peter and Carla worry about Daniel

episodes.name: Monday, 25th November 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: The police turn up to arrest abuser Kel, who’s been shopped by Bernie. But later, Kel takes his ex hostage at No.5... Chesney returns Daniel’s precious stolen laptop.

episodes.name: Monday, 25th November 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Ty and Fiz hold a fireworks party, where a fire starts in the backyard, leading them to fear Hope was behind It. Roy has a visit from his newfound brother, Richard.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 27th November 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Fiz and Tyrone head out while Jade stays home with the kids. Later, Fiz flips when she finds a lighter in Hope’s doll, and the terrible truth is revealed. Carla has a business idea.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 27th November 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Roy gets closer to Richard and angers Tina as he tries to help his poorly brother. Paul has counselling, and Michelle forges ahead with the plans for her wedding.

episodes.name: Friday, 29th November 2019
episodes.overview: Steve gets some good news. Adam advises Michelle to drop her plan to take the Bistro from Robert. She fumes when Robert lets slip he’s told Vicky about Ryan. When Fiz hears Hope is allowed to return to Bessie Street, she tells Jade that she’s no longer needed... Roy pushes Richard’s carer to quit because of her poor timekeeping.

episodes.name: Monday, 2nd December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: When Vicky vows to fleece Robert, Michelle persuades him to put the Bistro in her name instead. Robert visits Vicky to make sure she doesn't attend the wedding...

episodes.name: Monday, 2nd December 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Daniel is in bits as Craig turns up to return his stolen laptop, allowing the widower to watch Sinead's videos. Jade is deadpan as she moves out of No.9

episodes.name: Wednesday, 4th December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: It's Michelle and Robert's big day, but will the bride go through with her plan? Vicky's son, Tyler, storms the wedding and demands to know where his mum is...

episodes.name: Wednesday, 4th December 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Before his police interview, Paul bravely tells the shocked factory staff he was abused by Kel. Daniel pushes everyone away to be alone with Bertie and Sinead's videos.

episodes.name: Friday, 6th December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: After Paul has his interview with the police about Kel's abuse, his irate mum, Bernie, takes matters into her own hands. Rita's forced to cancel her trip away.

episodes.name: Friday, 6th December 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Robert accuses Tyler of reporting him to the police, and Michelle's questioned about Vicky's disappearance. When the police talk to Carla, she reveals Robert's violent past.

episodes.name: Monday, 9th December 2019
episodes.overview: Maria tells Gary she's pregnant, but a concerned Ali soon has a warning for her. Geoff and Yasmeen return from Vegas... and they've got married while away! Tim realises he's a bigamist. Ken, Peter and Adam are shocked by the state of Daniel's flat. Bernie sends Kel a message from Alfie.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 11th December 2019
episodes.overview: Daniel gets drunk and steps out in front of Cathy's car. Tim meets up with his other wife, Charlie. Maria confronts Gary about how he really makes his money. Michelle boots Robert out of the Bistro.

episodes.name: Friday, 13th December 2019
episodes.overview: Robert is arrested on suspicion of assault. Tim proposes to Sally. Geoff humiliates Yasmeen at their wedding party. Gemma and Chesney finally bring their quads home, but struggle to cope. Michael does a deal with Big Garth.

episodes.name: Monday, 16th December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Robert and Paula pick over the evidence against him, while Chesney and Gemma get by with a little help from their friends. Elsewhere, Tim discovers that his plan is fundamentally flawed.

episodes.name: Monday, 16th December 2019 (part 2)
episodes.overview: Michelle's revelations prompt the police to charge Robert, and Gemma feels under scrutiny during the Freshco photo shoot. Meanwhile, Roy shows an interest in Richard's hobby.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 18th December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Roy makes an error of judgement by leaving Richard unattended, and Michelle receives a mystery offer for the Bistro. Elsewhere, Ryan begs Gary for work to pay off his debt.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 18th December 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Nina lays the blame on Roy, and Michael waits in vain for a visit from Grace and Tianna. Elsewhere, Ryan completes a mission for Gary.

episodes.name: Friday, 20th December 2019
episodes.overview: Robert's court hearing is delayed when new information comes to light, and Gary gets wind of Derek's plot to sell the factory. Meanwhile, Roy attempts to make peace with Nina.

episodes.name: Monday, 23rd December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Nick and Sarah unveil the refurbished factory to the staff, keeping quiet about Derek's change of heart, while Sean reveals to an appalled Fiz that Jade is living on the streets. Rita tells Gemma she has arranged to visit Mavis over Christmas, despite the fact she has no plans to go anywhere. Emma and Seb become a couple, but will Alina ruin their romance?

episodes.name: Monday, 23rd December 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Gary lies to Maria that Derek ran into financial trouble, so he swooped in to save the factory and the workers' jobs. Later, he locks a tied-up Derek in the furniture shop overnight, determined to make sure he misses his flight to Florida with his kids. Fiz and Tyrone find Jade on Victoria Street and drag her back to No 9 and, while Rita decorates her tree alone, Emma informs Seb that Alina came looking for him.

episodes.name: Tuesday, December 24th 2019
episodes.overview: Gary frees Derek from his bonds, and Fiz calls at the furniture shop to drop off items from a house clearance, including a live antique gun. In the Rovers, a drunk Ali vows to win back Maria and see Gary get his comeuppance. Elsewhere, Marion rails at Shona and David for banning Max from seeing her.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 25th December 2019
episodes.overview: Gary's stunned to find the furniture shop door open, and the gun and its ammunition missing. A worse-for-wear Derek lurches into the Rovers looking for Windass, pulls out a gun and fires a shot. Shona's plan for David's treasure hunt is soon forgotten when she and the Platts find themselves in the middle of a shootout. And while Seb comes to a decision about his future with Emma, Michelle puts her affairs in order as she makes plans to leave Weatherfield.

episodes.name: Thursday, 26th December 2019
episodes.overview: Following one of the most dramatic Christmas Days in Weatherfield history, the long-suffering Street residents come to terms with the aftermath and try to get their lives back in order.

episodes.name: Friday, 27th December 2019
episodes.overview: Michelle heads to the bistro to hand over the keys to the new owner, but when the mystery buyer turns out to be Ray, she sets about smashing up the place. Elsewhere, Ali reveals that he's told the police about Gary's secret life as a loan shark, and a mortified Fiz confesses to Tyrone and Jade how she bought a gun for the shop, and it was then stolen.

episodes.name: Monday, 30th December 2019 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Gary's true colours are finally revealed. Ray goes into competition with the Rovers.

episodes.name: Monday, 30th December 2019 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Abi leaves Kevin disappointed. Tracy's grateful when Paula offers Amy some work experience.

episodes.name: Tuesday, 31st December 2019
episodes.overview: Tracy drowns her sorrows after a row with Steve. Ray offers Michelle's old job to Alya. The Barlows raise a toast to Sinead.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 1st January 2020
episodes.overview: Tracy realises she has cheated on Steve. There's a stand-off at the factory. Abi hurts Kevin's Feelings again.

episodes.name: Friday, 3rd January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Josh stands trial for raping David. Evelyn warns Fiz and Tyrone that there's something fishy about Jade.

episodes.name: Friday, 3rd January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Steve confronts Tracy - does he know about her fling?

episodes.name: Monday, 6th January 2020
episodes.overview: Fiz and Tyrone get a visit from social services, who have had reports about Hope being injured. Gary is taken in by the police to bow to Freshco's demands. Amy starts her work experience with Paula and demands a wage.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 8th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Fiz and Tyrone are questioned about the gun used in the shooting. Leanne overhears Tracy begging her lover to keep quiet.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 8th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Aggie is interviewed by a reporter about her Christmas Day heroics.

episodes.name: Friday, 10th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Sally's hot tub hosts an awkward reunion for Tracy, while Gemma and Chesney discover they are easily replaceable. Elsewhere, Aggie explains her change of career to Roy.

episodes.name: Friday, 10th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Tracy confesses all to a horrified Steve, and Bernie's meddling sends Dev into a rage. Meanwhile, Cathy confides in Brian about her concerns for Yasmeen.

episodes.name: Monday, 13th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Fiz tells the police the truth about the gun. Cathy worries about Yasmeen. Steve asks Tracy to marry him again.

episodes.name: Friday, 10th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Tracy confesses all to a horrified Steve, and Bernie's meddling sends Dev into a rage. Meanwhile, Cathy confides in Brian about her concerns for Yasmeen.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 15th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Geoff makes out that Yasmeen is an alcoholic • Fiz gets a suspended prison sentence and fine.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 15th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Shona opens her eyes but doesn't recognise David • Bernie tells Sean about her plan to get justice for Paul.

episodes.name: Friday, 17th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: David tries desperately to trigger Shona's memory • Bernie hunts down Kel, helped by Paul, Billy and Gemma.

episodes.name: Friday, 17th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Jade books oneway ferry tickets to France for her and Hope. Geoff manipulates Yasmeen into staying at home. Abi gets her GCSE results.

episodes.name: Monday, 20th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Tyrone and Evelyn are shocked when Ruby reveals that Jade put the bruises on Hope's arm with make-up, while Billy urges Paul to accept that Kel may never be punished for his crimes and to move on with his life. As an exhausted Gemma takes a nap with the quads, someone pushes a burning rag through the letterbox and a fire quickly takes hold.

episodes.name: Monday, 20th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Fiz returns home following Hope's disclosure, and Christine questions Jade, but she sticks to her story, accusing the flame-haired mum of abusing her daughter. Chesney arrives home to find flames licking at the door, David seeks Max's understanding, and when Kevin makes a snide remark about her landing herself a sugar daddy, Abi storms out.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 22nd January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Tyrone and Fiz are horrified to discover the back door unlocked and Hope gone. Tim's shocked to find Charlie on his doorstep, and she tells him he can forget about the divorce as she cannot afford the legal fees. Bethany is gutted when Alya reveals that Ray has made her the bistro's new manager.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 22nd January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Fiz shows the police the passports and ferry tickets, convinced Jade has abducted Hope. Carla tells an appalled Bethany how Ray made Michelle sign a gagging order, and Charlie returns to No 4 with her bags and explains she's been evicted.

episodes.name: Friday, 24th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Yasmeen finds Jade lying unconscious in the ginnel, and Fiz looks like the prime suspect. Charlie tells Tim how much cash she wants before she will sign any divorce papers. Bethany discusses career options with Daniel, but he suggests she might be best to leave Weatherfield altogether.

episodes.name: Friday, 24th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: The police wonder if Fiz can shed any light on Jade's assault, Daniel panics as he takes Bertie's temperature, and Bernie tells Paul that she is moving on. Meanwhile, Tim's plan to send Charlie on her way doesn't work out as planned when he finds her working at the Rovers.

episodes.name: Monday, 27th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel discovers Bertie barely conscious and urges Peter to call an ambulance. Maria insists Gary should go to Bristol.

episodes.name: Monday, 27th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Beth rails at Daniel for endangering Bertie's life. In an attempt to get the babies to sleep, Gemma suggests to Chesney that they take them for a walk.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 29th January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Gemma and Chesney realise they've been removed from the marketing campaign. Daniel thanks Bethany for helping him through a terrible ordeal.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 29th January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Imran advises a furious Gemma that there's nothing she can do about Freshco's advertising decisions.

episodes.name: Friday, 31st January 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Sally is horrified to find out that everyone knows Tim is a bigamist. Alya assures Yasmin that her drinking is fine. Geoff does his best to undermine Yasmeen's confidence.

episodes.name: Friday, 31st January 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Daniel confuses Bethany for Sinead and kisses her. Geoff spreads lies about Yasmeen's drinking.

episodes.name: Monday, 3rd February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Geoff is fuming when his trick does not work, and Maria explains to Liam she has lost the baby. When a dishevelled Nina calls in at the cafe. Roy's pleased to see her while Carla is concerned.

episodes.name: Monday, 3rd February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Tim is surprised to see his dad can't see the funny side over the botched trick, and Gary assures Maria that he wants to be with her, baby or not. Steve and Tracy decide it's time to be honest with each other, and Sarah warns Bethany to tread carefully after sleeping with Daniel.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 5th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Geoff locks a terrified Yasmin in his magic box. Nina admits to Roy and Carla that she's homeless.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 5th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Bethany refuses to bow to Roy's demands. Time tries and fails, to worm his way back in with Sally.

episodes.name: Friday, 7th February 2020
episodes.overview: In a special episode - Corrie's 10,000 show - Rita discovers her ex-husband Dennis has died and is supported by friends as she heads to Blackpool to spread his ashes. But, the trip doesn't go according to plan.....

episodes.name: Monday, 10th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Bethany warns Alya that Ray is probably trying to get her into bed, an exhausted David crashes while taking the kids to the school play, and Eileen calls in the factory, hoping to apply for the Customer Services job.

episodes.name: Monday, 10th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Having downloaded Ray's legal files, Bethany and Daniel find a list of names including Michelle's with an asterisk next to them. David, Max and Lily extract themselves from the car wreckage, while Eileen and Alina are interviewed for the Underworld job.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 12th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Ray tries to convince Alya that he did not have designs on her, and David is devastated when the doctor reveals Shona does not want to see him. When Alina reveals that she's looking for somewhere to live, Seb suggests to Emma that she could move in with them.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 12th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Abi is shocked to hear the allegations about Ray, while Maria hands David her keys, telling him she would like him to have her car. Ryan hands Gary an envelope full of cash and confirms it's the last of his debt collections.

episodes.name: Friday, 14th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Maria voices her suspicions to Ali about Gary, while Tim, Sally and Abi discuss the online article exposing Ray as a sex pest. Beth tears a strip off Daniel and Bethany for jumping into bed together when Sinead's only been dead a few months.

episodes.name: Friday, 14th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Maria confronts Gary about his shady dealings, Abi turns up at the charity gala with a plan, while Daniel tells the Rovers regulars that he and Bethany are now an item. Elsewhere, Sarah and Adam broach the subject of their wedding with David.

episodes.name: Monday, 17th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Ray tells Abi he's reported her to the police for stealing his car and torching it. Knowing the house to be empty, James takes Danny back to No 3 and leads him up the stairs. And Gemma's horrified to realise the Freshco photoshoot clashes with Aled's hearing appointment.

episodes.name: Monday, 17th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Ali calls at Maria's flat and begs her to give their relationship a chance, convinced she feels the same way about him. Gemma tells Chesney that Frescho will have to reschedule the photoshoot as Aled's doctor's appointment is far more important, and it looks like Ed may discover Danny and James's relationship.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 19th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Ali calls at Maria's flat and begs her to give their relationship a chance, convinced she feels the same way about him. Gemma tells Chesney that Frescho will have to reschedule the photoshoot as Aled's doctor's appointment is far more important, and it looks like Ed may discover Danny and James's relationship.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 19th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Tara tells Chesney that he's trashed the Freshco's brand and she's terminating their contract, Ed is convinced that Danny has corrupted James, and Maria tells a thrilled Gary that she'd love to marry him.

episodes.name: Friday, 21st February 2020
episodes.overview: Chesney panics when Joseph goes missing, and Ali begs Maria not to marry Gary. After spending the night with Kevin, Abi's cautious about confusing Jack, and Adam's not pleased to learn that Sarah's invited the whole factory to their wedding.

episodes.name: Monday, 24th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: An upbeat James looks forward to meeting Danny later, Bethany tells Sarah she believes Ray is blocking all her attempts to get restaurant jobs, and when Ray gets Abi alone in the garage he reveals that a friend's dashcam footage shows her stealing his car.

episodes.name: Monday, 24th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Sarah informs Beth that Bethany will be starting work at the factory tomorrow and she expects her to be made welcome, Danny tells James he doesn't want to continue seeing him, and as Kevin awaits Abi's arrival for tea he is shocked to find Ray on his doorstep.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 26th February 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Kevin confesses to Tyrone that he's being blackmailed by Ray, Gemma attends a baby senses class with the quads, and Peter calls at No.1 with the intention of telling Ken that he no longer wants the house.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 26th February 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Sarah implores Bethany not to let her feelings for Daniel stand in the way of her career, Vanessa suggests Gemma should come to her baby yoga class, and Tyrone is furious with Kevin for putting their business in jeopardy to help Abi

episodes.name: Friday, 28th February 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff returns home and rails at Yasmeen for failing to have his dinner on the table, and when she explains she was cleaning out the chicken coop and lost track of time, his mood darkens. Sally invites Kevin round for dinner with Abi before heading off to Sarah's hen night and leaving them to sort out their differences, and Tracy urges Steve to up their offer on the house in the hope that it'll top Peter's bid.

episodes.name: Monday, 2nd March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel bags up Sinead's belongings for Beth. Alya seeks the true story behind Yasmeen's tears. Sarah and Bethany remain at loggerheads.

episodes.name: Monday, 2nd March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: The Barlows and Platts convene for Adam and Sarah's wedding. Yasmeen's absence sends Geoff into a panic. Jade gets short shrift from Tyrone.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 4th March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel resolves to prove his devotion to Bethany. Tyrone's act of kindness misleads Jade. Geoff offers to pay for Sally and Tim's wedding.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 4th March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Bethany realises the time has come to leave Weatherfield. Tyrone and Fiz unite against Jade. Adam dupes Ali into revealing his fling with Maria.

episodes.name: Friday, 6th March 2020
episodes.overview: Gary reels when he runs into Adam, who can't resist sharing some information he has learnt about Maria and Ali. When Gary asks Ryan if it's true, a scared Ryan denies it. Ryan later tells Ali that he's saved his bacon. Craig vows to get fit.

episodes.name: Monday, 9th March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Gary asks Sharon to teach Ali a lesson, and a reporter asks James about rumours regarding his sexuality circulating on social media. Roy's fellow bat-watchers are horrified by Nina's attire and deeply suspicious of her motives.

episodes.name: Monday, 9th March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: A terrified Gary leaves a message for Sharon telling her that if Ali dies, she is to blame, and James receives a worrying text from his manager. Roy resigns from the bat-watching group after some of the members' remarks about Nina's dress sense.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 11th March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Ali assures Ryan that Gary, or someone hired by Windass, must have spiked his drink, and Alya confronts Geoff about her belief he is behind the nasty online reviews for Speed Daal. Aggie reveals that they've had several calls from newspapers wanting to get James's side of the story.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 11th March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: James lies to his Manager and Press Officer and assures them he is not gay, and Ali takes Maria on a terrifying car ride. Meanwhile, Nina wonders if Roy's ashamed to be seen with her after claiming the meeting with the bat group has been cancelled.

episodes.name: Friday, 13th March 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff tries to persuade Yasmeen that Alya is out to get him, while Gary convinces Maria that he did nothing to provoke Ali and that the guy is a maniac. Audrey worries that Ken is being railroaded into moving to Stillwaters against his will, and Imran puts pressure on Toyah to find a new job.

episodes.name: Monday, 16th March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Alya learns that Geoff and Yasmeen intend to sell up and move away. Claudia volunteers Ken to give a talk to their new neighbours. Bernie returns to find Gemma struggling to cope.

episodes.name: Monday, 16th March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Evelyn bumps into her ex-boyfriend Arthur at the vets. Alya begs Yasmeen to leave controlling Geoff. Norris fills Ken in on life at Stillwaters.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 18th March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Alya discovers Geoff has a violent past. Gemma's upset when Imogen and Vanessa lie to her.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 18th March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Emma decides to play it cool with Seb. Evelyn and Arthur reminisce about how they almost tied the knot.

episodes.name: Friday, 20th March 2020
episodes.overview: David discovers Shona has been in contact with Clayton. Gemma breaks down after the quads are put in danger. Yasmeen turns her back on Alya. Emma fears Seb is still into Alina. Evelyn prepares for a date with old flame Arthur, with a little help from Claudia.

episodes.name: Monday, 23rd March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: It becomes clear that Gemma is not coping with motherhood and even the health visitor question her about her state of mind. But later, as the babies' crying escalates, she heads into the yard to calm herself - and realises with horror she is locked out. Alya introduces Yasmeen to a police officer who has information about Geoff - but scared, she refuses to listen and rushed out. David begs Clayton to leave Shona alone, Tyrone gives Arthur a piece of his mind for standing Evelyn up, and Norris reluctantly joins Ken for the Stillwaters' art class.

episodes.name: Monday, 23rd March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Bernie arrives to find Gemma in such a distressed state, so she agrees to move in and help with the babies - on the condition that she doesn't tell Chesney that Gemma isn't coping. Nick tries to talk to Shona but she refuses to see him, passing on a message to David instead. Arthur apologises to Evelyn and asks her to give him another chance, and Ken and Norris sneak out to the Rovers for a treat.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 25th March 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: David is devastated about Shona's divorce request but claims it will give him a chance to move on - and when he finds Alina alone in Victoria Garden, it is clear there is a spark between them. News of a family wedding gives Alya the chance she needs to get Yasmeen away from Geoff. The only problem is, they are not invited. Bernie forces Gemma to seek medical help, Evelyn summons Claudia for another makeover and Charles is outraged to discover Ken has smuggled Eccles the dog into his apartment.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 25th March 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: An argument in the Rovers turns to blows when David accuses Seb of being jealous of his friendship with Alina - and when Emma realises her boyfriend still has feeling for his ex, she tells him to find somewhere else to stay. Gemma plays down her depression and assures the doctor she is just exhausted, leaving Bernie frustrated by her daughter's refusal to accept help. Alya and Ryan tell Yasmeen they have been invited to Zeedan's wedding in Spain. Now all they have to do is tell Geoff, who is not on the guest list.

episodes.name: Monday, 30th March 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff feigns illness to sabotage Yasmeen's plans. Seb pledges his heart to Emma. Reckless David places himself in harm's way.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 1st April 2020
episodes.overview: Alya tackles Geoff about his lies. David flees from a group of muggers. Ken demands a copy of the Stillwaters rule book from Charles.

episodes.name: Friday, 3rd April 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen confronts Geoff with the contents of his emails, Gemma tries to be positive as Aled's hearing aid is fitted and David apologises for using Alina.

episodes.name: Monday, 6th April 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff despairs as Yasmeen walks out on him, Bernie implores Chesney to keep a close eye on Gemma, and Michael attends a job interview at Underworld. David heads out for a walk, but when Gail quizzes him, he refuses to tell her where he's going.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 8th April 2020
episodes.overview: Gemma boards the bus with the quads, but is suddenly overcome by a wave of anxiety and hurries off the bus, leaving her babies behind. The return of Rick's daughter Kelly rattles Gary, and Yasmeen consults the police about Geoff's past.

episodes.name: Friday, 10th April 2020
episodes.overview: Steve regrets prioritising Emma's needs over Oliver's, Gemma returns home and finally admits to Chesney that she thinks she's a terrible mother and no longer feels in control, while Ken decides to challenge Charles' supremacy.

episodes.name: Monday, 13th April 2020
episodes.overview: Leanne is livid to learn Steve left Oliver with Summer. Gemma is diagnosed with postnatal depression. Ken's Still waters election campaign gets off to a bad start. May and Asha are love rivals.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 15th April 2020
episodes.overview: Naked photos of Asha are posted to a group chat. Leanne discovers Steve is taking legal advice about Oliver. Johnny is unnerved by new B&B guest Scott. Charles challenges Ken to a fencing match.

episodes.name: Friday, 17th April 2020
episodes.overview: Asha's devastated to discover her pics have gone viral. Steve and Leanne row over Oliver. Johnny suggests a holiday to Jenny, in a bid to avoid Scott, Ken learns Charles has been ripping off the residents.

episodes.name: Monday, 20th April 2020
episodes.overview: Asha feels the eyes of the world on her. Ken publicly exposes Charles' financial fraud. Carla agrees to take charge at the Rovers.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 22nd April 2020
episodes.overview: Gary intervenes in Amy and Kelly's fight. Ken tells Claudia that Stillwaters will never be his home. Johnny feels uneasy leaving Scott at the Rovers.

episodes.name: Friday, 24th April 2020
episodes.overview: Cathy comes round for a natter but Geoff manipulates the situation so that Yasmeen ends up offending her and she storms out in a fury. Gary finds Kelly in tears. Asha implores Dev not to go to the police about the video.

episodes.name: Monday, 27th April 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen heads to the medical centre.  Geoff declares that Yasmeen caught the STI from Sharif. Kelly’s mum Laura visits Gary at the furniture shop.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 29th April 2020
episodes.overview: Daniel returns from the grief retreat and Ken’s pleased to hear he found it a great help. Dev see how distraught his daughter is and finally agrees to phone the school and try to withdraw his complaint.

episodes.name: Friday, 1st May 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen finally snaps after months of abuse. Yasmeen is shocked to discover Geoff has agreed to pay for their wedding.

episodes.name: Monday, 4th May 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen faces the consequences of her red mist, as the paramedics attend to Geoff. The police question the regulars about Geoff and Yasmeen’s relationship.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 6th May 2020
episodes.overview:
An exhausted Yasmeen sits in her police cell.

When Dev blames Kelly for heaping so much trouble on Asha, Gary leaps to Kelly’s defence leaving Adam intrigued.

A loved up Adam and Sarah return from their honeymoon.

episodes.name: Friday, 8th May 2020
episodes.overview:
Alya tells Sally that Geoff has been controlling Yasmeen for months and she’s never had a drink problem.  Imran watches as a bewildered and upset Yasmeen is charged.

Max delivers his speech at the Outreach Awards and looks with disappointment at David’s empty chair.

episodes.name: Monday 11th May 2020
episodes.overview:
Steve meets up with Leanne at the nursery school that they are looking at for Oliver and the head teacher offers to show them round.

Nervous Yasmeen attends her bail hearing and sees Imran take the stand as Geoff and Sally look on. Will she be granted bail?

Cathy complains to Dev about Bernie and threatens to leave the kebab shop. However when Dev offers her an extra 50p an hour, Cathy changes her mind.

episodes.name: Wednesday 13th May 2020
episodes.overview:
Steve and Leanne fear for their son after his seizure and describe Oliver’s symptoms to the doctor.

In the kebab shop, Cathy and Bernie bury the hatchet and Bernie agrees to knuckle down.

Alya calls at the Rovers and tells Sean how Yasmeen is the victim of domestic abuse and she is determined to take Geoff down.

episodes.name: Friday 15th May 2020
episodes.overview:
When Don makes another racist comment, Ed just lets it go leaving Michael confused.

To Steve and Leanne’s relief, Oliver seems much better.

Craig suggests to David they go for a run together and it’s clear David wants to get out of it.

episodes.name: Monday, 18th May 2020
episodes.overview: Steve and Leanne await the outcome of Oliver's tests. The Baileys display differing attitudes to racial abuse. Gemma realises that she's not alone.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 20th May 2020
episodes.overview:
Steve and Leanne Battersby keep a vigil at Oliver’s bedside. Having googled mitochondrial disease, Steve’s upbeat as he explains that there are different strains and many people with the disease lead full and normal lives.

Gemma tells Bernie and Chesney that she feels like she’s turned a corner and she couldn’t have done it without them and the support group.

episodes.name: Friday, 22nd May 2020
episodes.overview:
Ed has had enough and challenges him and as the room falls silent he explains he’s suffered racist abuse all his life, but he’ll never give up the fight to put a stop to it.

Michael assures Tianna that there’s no place in this world for racism and he’ll do everything he can to make it a better place for her.

Aggie tells Ed that she’s proud of him for standing up to Don but wishes she could be proud of the way he is with James too.

episodes.name: Monday, 25th May 2020
episodes.overview: Oliver has his sedation reduced. James faces his demons at football training. David seeks an outlet for his rage when he learns the latest about Shona.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 27th May 2020
episodes.overview: Clayton takes advantage of Shona's memory loss. Leanne insists that Oliver will make a full recovery. James worries that he made the wrong decision.

episodes.name: Friday, 29th May 2020
episodes.overview: Shona requests that David stays away during her home visit. Tim collects Geoff from hospital. Dev accuses Asha's school of failing to protect her.

episodes.name: Monday, 1st June 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff gains entry to Number 6 to delete the CCTV footage. Roy finds Shona lurking outside the cafe. Dev decides to move the twins to Oakhill School.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 3rd June 2020
episodes.overview: Alya makes a shocking discovery regarding Geoff. Asha's problems follow her to her new school. Roy invites Shona to move into his flat.

episodes.name: Friday, 5th June 2020
episodes.overview: Asha Alahan comes face to face with Corey and his cronies. Realising the truth will come out in court, Geoff admits he hired escorts as Yasmeen refused him sex. Roy and David visit Shona at the rehab centre.

episodes.name: Monday, 8th June 2020
episodes.overview: Whilst Gary Windass is doing a bit of investigation work with the help of a PI to try and find Kelly’s mum, Adam is doing his own digging, quizzing Kelly about her dad.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 10th June 2020
episodes.overview: To Alya’s delight Yasmeen Nazir enters a not guilty plea. Back on the street, Geoff is furious and tells Tim they need to show a united front.

episodes.name: Friday, 12th June 2020
episodes.overview: Sally tells Tim Metcalfe that she wants Geoff out – forcing him to move back to number 6. Tim feels bad but when Eileen also says she isn’t sure about Geoff’s side of things he starts to wonder about his dad’s protestations of innocence.

episodes.name: Monday, 15th June 2020
episodes.overview: Chelsey blackmails Carla to keep quiet about her past. Sally refuses to sit with Tim at The Rovers. Daniel realises how empty his life is. Adam cosies up to Laura, as Gary urges her to move away.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 17th June 2020
episodes.overview: Carla is confronted by lowlife Jordan. Daniel goes to a bash with Adam and meets a woman called Nicky. Roy tells David that Shona's being discharged from the rehab centre. Faye is angry to discover that Sally and Tim threw Geoff out.

episodes.name: Friday, 19th June 2020
episodes.overview: Carla fronts up to Chelsey and Jordan. Scott hides a secret. Daniel agrees to a night with Nicky. David prepares for Shona's return to Weatherfield. Faye announces she's moving in with her grandad Geoff.

episodes.name: Monday, 22nd June 2020
episodes.overview: Daniel lies to Adam about his evening with Nicky. Tracy persuades Leanne to grant Oliver a trip out. Carla thanks Abi for her show of support.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 24th June 2020
episodes.overview: David decides to take Shona to the Bistro for dinner, which proves too much for his Mum. He's amused when she reveals that she has stolen Ray's wallet. When Carla accuses Peter of beating up Jordan and Chelsey, he's offended and denies it. Daniel opens up to Nicky about Sinead, admitting how lonely he's become.

episodes.name: Friday, 26th June 2020
episodes.overview: After Gemma tells Shona what a great relationship she had with David, Shona invites her hubby over. David is pleased, but then shocked when she tries to kiss him! There's some bad news that floors Steve and Leanne. Jenny returns from France - without Johnny. Fiz and Tyrone have a date night at home.

episodes.name: Monday, 29th June 2020
episodes.overview: Leanne rejects Oliver's devastating diagnosis. Toyah and Imran celebrate some promising feedback. Alina's loyalty to Emma is tested.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 1st July 2020
episodes.overview: Simon is wounded by Leanne's thoughtless words. Toyah sticks to her decision to abandon fostering. Fiz offers Chesney relationship tips.

episodes.name: Friday, 3rd July 2020
episodes.overview: Nick defends Leanne from Peter's criticism, and Jenny explains to Scott why Johnny stayed in France. Meanwhile, gatecrashers disturb Fiz and Tyrone's romantic evening.

episodes.name: Monday, 6th July 2020
episodes.overview: When Toyah calls round to offer support, Leanne turns on her, insisting she has no idea how she's feeling. Sally's appalled to learn from Cathy how Geoff locked Yasmeen in his magic box. And when Michael reveals that he's got a date with Grace at the bistro, Aggie warns him not to get involved.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 8th July 2020
episodes.overview: Nick suggests to Leanne that they should go to a support group for parents of terminally ill children, Tim is shocked to find out that Sally has visited Yasmeen, and Roy apologises for upsetting Evelyn.

episodes.name: Friday, 10th July 2020
episodes.overview: Toyah accepts Leanne's apology for the awful things she said and introduces her sister to someone who may be able to help her. Abi blocks out the past. Much to Alya's dismay, Geoff returns to work at Speed Daal. He the secretly pinches her phone when he learns she's expecting a call from Yasmeen.

episodes.name: Monday 13th July, 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff offers to drop his complaint against Yasmeen. Imran confides in Nick about his plans with Toyah. Aggie appeals to Grace on Michael's behalf.

episodes.name: Wednesday 15th July, 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff's latest manipulation of Yasmeen horrifies Alya. Abi informs Seb that the twins are moving abroad. Carla decides to get back to business.

episodes.name: Friday 17th July, 2020
episodes.overview: Kevin invites Abi to move in to Number 13. Carla returns to her old stomping ground. Geoff is shocked to receive a call from Yasmeen.

episodes.name: Monday, 20th July 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff uses his hospital radio show to talk about how he has forgiven Yasmeen and wants to help her. Abi moves into No 13, and when Adam spots Sinead's cardigan poking out of his bag, Daniel is embarrassed.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 22nd July 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen phones Geoff with a surprising message, and Adam suspects that Gary has killed Rick. Nicky informs Daniel they could do more than talk for the money he's paying her.

episodes.name: Friday, 24th July 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen collapses on the first day of her trial, and Gary is concerned by Brian's interest in Beacon Woods because of a potential stash of Roman coins. Meanwhile, Ed worries that Aggie is working far too hard at the hospital.

episodes.name: Monday, 27th July 2020
episodes.overview: Yasmeen wakes up after a heart attack, and Brian is annoyed that Bernie found a watch in the woods and sold it to Sarah. Meanwhile, Abi tells Ed that Aggie can use Kevin's car until hers is fixed as the neighbourhood is grateful for putting herself on the front line at the hospital.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 29th July 2020
episodes.overview: Ed is gutted that Aggie has to isolate at a hotel on their 30th wedding anniversary, and Sarah demands to know if Gary killed Rick, before he is hit by a car. Elaine calls Alya and confirms that she's prepared to give evidence against Geoff.

episodes.name: Friday, 31st July 2020
episodes.overview: Gary fights for his life, and Adam senses Sarah is lying about her showdown with her ex. Meanwhile, Alya implores Elaine not to leave as she is the only hope of securing Yasmeen's freedom, and Ed sits down to a virtual anniversary dinner with Aggie via video call.

episodes.name: Monday, 3rd August 2020
episodes.overview: Police ask Sarah about the accident, and why she called 999 before the collision happened. In Roy's Rolls, Elaine introduces herself to Sally, and explains that she is Tim's mother. And Jenny sympathizes with Abi over the twins' imminent departure for Australia.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 5th August 2020
episodes.overview: Sally implores Tim to accept that Elaine could be telling the truth and Geoff could have fed him a pack of lies all his life. Elsewhere, Leanne is overwhelmed with grief, and when Carla lets slip that Gary's binned his threat of a rent increase, Maria's concerned.

episodes.name: Friday, 7th August 2020
episodes.overview: Geoff swears that Elaine is peddling lies, she's not Tim's Mum and Alya must have put her up to it in a bid to drive a wedge between them. Leanne urges Toyah to set the fostering wheels in motion as she deserves some happiness. And Adam seethes when Sarah fails to mention Gary's change of heart over the rent.

episodes.name: Monday, 10th August 2020
episodes.overview: Bernie tells Adam the saga of Rick's watch. Alya resolves to sell Speed Daal to escape Geoff. Nina bears the brunt of Steve's emotional turmoil.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 12th August 2020
episodes.overview: Adam orders Sarah to reveal all she knows about Gary's misdeeds. Leanne offers Steve a shoulder to cry on. Gemma hears from an old adversary.

episodes.name: Friday, 14th August 2020
episodes.overview: Gary fears that Sarah has shared his darkest secrets, Maria asks David to witness her wedding instead of a sick Audrey, and a spiteful Geoff tells Sally that Tim will always choose him over her.

episodes.name: Monday, 17th August 2020
episodes.overview: Gary's feelings for Sarah threaten his wedding to Maria. Tim puts some distance between him and Geoff. Gemma announces a new project.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 19th August 2020
episodes.overview: Disaster strikes as Abi prepares for a final farewell with the twins. Sean and Mary are shocked to hear from Todd. Billy and Gemma plan a surprise for Paul.

episodes.name: Friday, 21st August 2020
episodes.overview: Seb is shocked to discover Abi is in hospital, and Mary, Sean and Billy stake out Victoria Garden, waiting for Todd to approach the money bag. While Gemma tries to keep Paul's party a secret, Daniel's obsession with Nicky continues, much to her discomfort

episodes.name: Monday, 24th August 2020
episodes.overview: Peter gets in the way of Abi's morphine fix. Sean and Billy report Todd's disappearance to the police. Nicky puts Danie in touch with another escort.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 26th August 2020
episodes.overview: Carla is suspicious when Peter lies to her about going to meet Abi, and when she finds out he is helping her with her addiction, she warns him to be careful. When Gemma presents Paul with a signed photo of PJ and Duncan, Paul can hardly believe his eyes, while Jenny greets Johnny's return with hostility.

episodes.name: Friday, 28th August 2020
episodes.overview: Alya taunts Geoff by revealing Yasmeen is fighting fit. Scott tells Johnny that they need to talk. Debble is suspicious of Abi. Daniel's wounded to see Nicky with another client. Sean's devastated to discover a man's body has been found in the canal.

episodes.name: Monday, 31st August 2020
episodes.overview: Johnny and Scott discuss the crime they committed. Daniel asks Adam to help Nicky. Geoff riles Alyaa. Debbie is suspicious to see Abi with Peter. Billy spots something on the missing-persons website

episodes.name: Wednesday, 2nd September 2020
episodes.overview: Alya reaches breaking point. David goes for a walk with Shona, but it doesn't go to plan. Asha helps a stressed-out Dev. Daniel persuades Nicky to have a drink with him, as pals.

episodes.name: Friday, 4th September 2020
episodes.overview: Tim starts to wonder if Geoff is as innocent as he claims he is. Adam pays Nicky to stay away from Daniel. David reassures an upset Shona. Mary and Cathy discuss Dev's money woes. Sean continues to worry about missing Todd.

episodes.name: Monday, 7th September 2020
episodes.overview: Sally takes a risk to get her hands on Geoff's laptop. Dev's decision to sell the kebab shop sparks concern. Shona's behaviour tests David's patience.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 9th September 2020
episodes.overview: Sally, Tim and Faye try to download Geoff's CCTV footage. David fears Shona will never return to normal. Asha blames herself for Dev's woes.

episodes.name: Friday, 11th September 2020
episodes.overview: David and Shona return to the Street but face further upheaval. Billy breaks the news to Paul that a body's been found in the canal and that it could be Kel's.

episodes.name: Monday, 14th September 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: There's heartache for Leanne when she receives an upsetting medical update about Oliver. Nick's left reeling when certain suspicions are confirmed.

episodes.name: Monday, 14th September 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: David and Shona return to the Street but face further upheaval. Billy breaks the news to Paul that a body's been found in the canal and that it could be Kel's.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 16th September 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: David tells Shona he's selling his house, but Shona has some news that could change everything... A desperate Leanne sets her heart on getting Oliver treatment abroad.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 16th September 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Abi is overwhelmed with guilt and comes clean to Debbie, admitting her drug addiction has been reignited. Paul and Billy get a visit from the police about Kel's death.

episodes.name: Friday, 18th September 2020
episodes.overview: Abi plucks up the courage to tell Kevin the truth about her addiction demons. How will he react? Steve tells Tracy and Emma how much Oliver's treatment will cost. Paul is shocked when he realises Billy suspected him of killing Kel. Kirk's convinced Daniel has got a new girlfriend when he spots him enjoying a drink with Nicky.

episodes.name: Monday, 21st September 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel sleeps with Nicky. Billy tells Mary he's hired a PI to find Todd. Nick keeps quiet about son Sam.

episodes.name: Monday, 21st September 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Debbie spots Abi and Peter in the ginnel. Steve has a plan to raise money for Oliver.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 23rd September 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Daniel pursues a romantic relationship with Nicky. Debbie warns Peter to steer clear of Abi. Billy's private investigator shares alarming news of Todd.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 23rd September 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Abi persuades Peter to keep her secret from Carla. Daniel's torment over Nicky leads to a row with Geoff. Grace defends Michael from criticism.

episodes.name: Friday, 25th September 2020
episodes.overview: Debbie tells Kevin that Abi and Peter are having an affair. Billy and Paul begin to regret their actions. Adam becomes suspicious of Daniel.

episodes.name: Monday, 28th September 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Michael plans a romantic proposal for Grace. Geoff refuses to give up the search for his missing money. Sarah lets slip Nick's secret to David.

episodes.name: Monday, 28th September 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Grace stuns Michael with an announcement. Daniel feels the long arm of the law. Carla and Peter acknowledge the fault lines in their relationship.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 30th September 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Michael takes action to stop Grace and Tianna from leaving. Carla gets involved in Sarah and Adam's marriage. Nick tries to offload Underworld.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 30th September 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Michael faces police questioning. Carla encourages Sarah to reconcile with Adam. Daniel offers Geoff an apology through gritted teeth.

episodes.name: Friday, 2nd October 2020
episodes.overview: Nick meets his son, while Leanne hears more bad news about hers. Billy catches out Paul in a lie. Grace implores Michael to make a fresh start.

episodes.name: Monday, 5th October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Steve and Leanne join forces to give Oliver a fighting chance. Billy confides his worries about Paul to David. Sally and Tim plan a secret wedding.

episodes.name: Monday, 5th October 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Tracy drops a bombshell on Steve. Tim orders Geoff to stay away from his wedding. Billy updates Eileen on the search for Todd.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 7th October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: A suspicious Leanne pries the truth out of Nick. Sally and Tim fear that Geoff will derail their big day. Sean disturbs an intruder at No. 11.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 7th October 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Leanne reels from Nick's confession that he has a son. The police turn up at the Metcalfe's wedding. Eileen discovers a note outside her back door.

episodes.name: Friday, 9th October 2020
episodes.overview: Eileen keeps quiet about her appointment with Todd. Johnny suspects that Scott is behind a local robbery. David moves Shona back into Number 8.

episodes.name: Monday, 12th October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Todd asks the impossible of Eileen to save his skin. Johnny gives Ray a warning about Scott. Maria questions Gary over their finances.

episodes.name: Monday, 12th October 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Eileen shares her dilemma with Mary. Ray makes Gary an offer for the factory premises. Scott insists that Johnny owes him a big favour.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 14th October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Mary and George suggest a drastic solution to Eileen. Gary does some digging on Ray. Evelyn and Arthur's early return puzzles Tyrone.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 14th October 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Todd brings danger to Eileen's door. Ray increases his offer when Gary turns him down. Evelyn asks Arthur to give her another chance.

episodes.name: Friday, 16th October 2020
episodes.overview: Gary receives a beating from Todd's nemesis. Shona takes the clippers to one of David's customers. Evelyn clashes with Dev over a holiday request.

episodes.name: Monday, 19th October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Mary investigates the noises in Eileen's loft. David dreads taking sole responsibility for Shona. Gary convinces Ray that he could be an asset to him.

episodes.name: Monday, 19th October 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: The secret of Todd's hiding place is out. The Winter Browns' job hunt proves unexpectedly successful. Ray gives Gary his first task.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 21st October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Todd's return causes heartache for Paul and Billy. David is troubled by a threat to his livelihood. Nick incurs Leanne's wrath.

episodes.name: Wednesday, 21st October 2020 (Part 2)
episodes.overview: Todd urges Billy to leave Paul and reunite with him. Gary encourages David to sell his house. Leanne gives an interview about Oliver's case.

episodes.name: Friday, 23rd October 2020 (Part 1)
episodes.overview: Billy assures Paul that his feelings have not changed. Natasha makes Nick a generous offer. Scott outlines the details of the robbery to Johnny.
